Command-line interfaces utilize mainly text, in which users operate the system by typing commands. Command-line interfaces are more complex in that specific commands must be accurate to work. CLIs are most commonly used for managing files and writing scripts.
Graphical user interfaces mainly function by providing visual elements, including icons and buttons. The visual elements are especially useful for users new to an interface. GUIs require items like a mouse and keyboard. GUIs are often considered easier to learn to use and can include images, videos, and animations. Gui’s are more customizable than CLIs.
